{
  "texts": [
    "Each study, employing a range of DL techniques from CNNs to Siamese neural networks, demonstrates significant advancements in the automated classification of fossils.",
    "These methods have not only show the potential to streamline traditional processes but have also introduced innovative approaches to tackling the inherent challenges of fossil classification, such as dealing with disparate morphologies and adapting to varying imaging conditions.",
    "Despite notable advancements, challenges such as model generalization, dataset diversity, and handling closely resembling species persist.",
    "These limitations can be overcome through methodological refinement, dataset expansion, and integrating sophisticated data processing techniques.",
    "This subsection reviews the DL-based methods for fossil instance segmentation."
  ]
}